DATA CLOUD
Connect Tableau in Data Cloud

Set up a connection to Data Cloud from Tableau. Different steps are required depending on which Tableau product and version you use.

As of the February 2024 release, you can no longer access the Customer Data Platform (CDP) connector from the Tableau Desktop and Tableau Cloud user interface because it’s deprecated. If you’re using the deprecated CDP connector, you can continue to access your existing data sources and workbooks, but you can’t create new data sources using the deprecated connector. Instead, use the Salesforce Data Cloud connector.

You can connect to these Tableau products from Data Cloud using the Salesforce Data Cloud connector.

Tableau Server helps to organize and share Tableau dashboards and workbooks. Using the Salesforce Data Cloud connector requires Tableau Server version 2023.3. Starting with version 2024.2, the Customer Data Platform connector is hidden in the user interface. See Connect Tableau Server to the Data Cloud.
Tableau Desktop is a visualization tool that turns your customer data into interactive visual representations like dashboards and workbooks. Using the Salesforce Data Cloud connector requires Tableau Desktop version 2023.2 or later. Starting with version 2024.1, the Customer Data Platform connector is hidden in the user interface. See Connect Tableau Desktop to the Data Cloud.
Tableau Prep cleans and shapes customer data to optimize analysis. Using the Salesforce Data Cloud connector requires Prep Web Authoring, Conductor version 2023.2, or Prep Builder 2023.2. See Connect to the Data Cloud.
Tableau Cloud is used for authoring, sharing, distributing, and collaborating on content. See Connect Tableau Cloud to the Data Cloud.
